Not positive, but...Looks like "Wyruna".  Built for the Duttons of "Anlibby" Station (Victoria) in 1908.  She was a gaff rigged day sailer built for Port Phillip Bay.  Later converted to Ketch rig with "leg o mutton main.
Fell off her stocks under refit in Melbourne and was scrapped.
